result.execSummary:
The defendant Anthony M Huebner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Use a Computer to Facilitate a Child Sex Crime [Modifiers: Repeater], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.075(1r).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: On Count #1 the Court sentences Mr. Huebner to 16 years & 6 months, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 11 years & 6 months, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 5  years. This sentence is to commence  FORTHWITH, concurrent to current sentence.

superMiscConds.notes: --to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge

--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as required by the Agent
--no contact with E.C. (dob: 5/13/2000) or the parents of E.C., Carolyn or Eric Cullison

The Court finds that Mr. Huebner already has a DNA sample on file, therefore does NOT order a DNA sample to be provided. 

Arresting Agency:  JCSD

If probation, parole or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of the victim(s) and government entities for the balance due.

****COURT ORDERS OUTRIGHT****
The Court orders Mr. Huebner to register as a sex offender pursuant to 301.45

Case called at 12:32pm [mo]
Defendant Anthony M Huebner in court, in custody with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa.   ADA Jeffrey Shock appears for the State of Wisconsin.

Constitutional rights reviewed; maximum penalties recited; plea of "No Contest" entered on Count #1 of the Amended Information; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Mr. Huebner  guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court recites the Jury Instructions for charges

On Joint Motion of the Parties, the Court reads-in and dismisses: Count #2

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel 

On Count #1 the Court sentences Mr. Huebner  to  16  years & 6 months, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  11  years & 6 months, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 5  years. 
This sentence is to commence  FORTHWITH, concurrent to current sentence. 

The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
 
The Court orders Mr. Huebner to register as a sex offender pursuant to 301.45

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as required by the Agent
--to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge
--no contact with E.C. (dob: 5/13/2000) or the parents of E.C., Carolyn or Eric Cullison

The Court finds that Mr. Huebner already has a DNA sample on file, therefore does NOT order a DNA sample to be provided. 
Felony Firearm and Voting-rights prohibitions/warnings given
Explanation of Determinate Sentence form given to the Defendant

The Court gives  0   days credit for time already served.
